description.$t: I'm a nice boy named Adrian. I came to the House of Mews with my 3 sisters and 1 brother (Trini, Trudy, Toni and Tansey)--whew--get me out of here! I am a shy, but loving boy who likes affection. I also love to be brushed and petted and I l-o-v-e to play! When you brush me--and eventually stop--I will reach out my paw to get your hand back over here brushing me where it belongs! I also flop onto the ground and won't go anywhere if you keep on brushing me! I am even learning how to like to be picked up, and yes, even cuddled. I started out very shy, but I have come out of my shell a lot. Aren't I good-looking too? Approx. DOB is 03/24/06.

I'm Dick and I am unique because I am at least part Manx with the c-u-t-e-s-t stub tail! Check it out! I am affectionate and love attention, and love to roll around on my back while you pet my tummy. I can be somewhat of a shy cat, but don't worry, I am a lovebug and have made huge strides coming out of my shell since I came to live at The House of Mews... everyone loves me. I have a soft meow and like to give soft head butts. I'll follow you around begging for attention, and I love to be brushed. I'm super playful too and I love a toy on a stick! Oh, and canned food too. My mother Eliza and my brother Harry live here at The House of Mews too! Harry and I love greeting visitors! Approx. DOB is 12-21-00.

First off, I have no idea why my name is Bad Boy...I am not a bad boy at all! Someone just gave me that silly name. I am a shy, but loving gray tabby who needs another chance at a nice home. Although I can be cautious, once I warm up to you I enjoy being petted. I especially like my head scratched.... mmmm.... that feels good! I can even be a little playful sometimes. My brother, Big Boy, and I have been at the House of Mews a long time and just want to find a new forever family. Won't you please come check us out? Approx. DOB is 12/16/00.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - gray and white

description.$t: I'm Hurley--you may think I am a boy because of that boy on that TV show "Lost"--but I am in fact a *very* sweet girl. But I am somewhat lost myself and need to find a new forever home. I was found in a park where people were trying to poison us kitties! I can be a little shy, but curious and friendly, and I CRAVE your attention and love being petted and brushed! When you come visit The House of Mews, you can be sure I will be meowing for your attention and will follow you around after I get it! I am voluptuous and have HUGE eyes. Please give me a second chance and I know we will become best friends. Look at my face....can you resist? Approx. DOB is 9-24-02.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - orange and white

description.$t: I'm Cinderella, a petite orange and white adorable kitty. I am a shy, sweet girl who tries not to let my shyness get in the way of your attention. I like to be petted and brushed, and with time and lots of love and patience, I will make a wonderful friend for you. When you pet me I wriggle around all over and rub my face all over too--not to mention p-u-r-r-i-n-g and a few cute little meows. That means I love it! I love a bit of canned food too and am really cute when I am "asking" for it. I need to be adopted with my best friend forever, Bonita. We can frequently be found curled up together in a basket, like in our picture. She looks a lot like me but we're cousins, so that's not too surprising. She's the only family I have right now since my mom went over the rainbow bridge. I am the lighter colored one, and she is a bit darker orange. Please don't overlook us just because we are shy. Approx DOB is 4/1/03.

I'm Fredo, a very handsome orange tabby. I am a little shy right now, but maybe I just need a nice, loving home of my own to let my personality bloom and blossom. Wait, that sounds too girly.... Well, I am currently residing in living quarters with ALL GIRLS! I actually have opened up a LOT since moving in here and I can be a real love bug. I really love to be brushed and will rub all around your legs while you are brushing me. I am sweet, curious, and I like treats. Anyway, hopefully someone will give me a chance to be a wonderful friend for you. Please don't overlook me just because I am a little shy. Approx. DOB is 2/2/07.

I'm Ansel, a black and white tuxedo cat with beautiful markings, and long white whiskers. I am shy, so I need lots of love and attention to further on my developing personality. I was quite afraid of people when I first came to the House of Mews, but now I get along well with other cats and am working on getting more comfortable around humans. But I think they just call that "aloof" right? I am learning to be petted more and more. I like a good head scratching (especially when canned food or treats are involved--hint hint). I meow-meow-meow when canned food is being served up. I think that with a good home with patient people, I may open up and become a bit more affectionate. I like to play with toys on sticks sometimes too. I enjoy basking in the sun in the front window of the House of Mews. Sometimes I eat and drink with my paw...it's really cute. Approx. DOB is 06/14/99.

THIS CAT IS CURRENTLY BEING FOSTERED. CONTACT US IF INTERESTED IN ADOPTION. I'm Seneca and I C-R-A-V-E your attention! I am a large lovebug who LOVES to be petted and brushed. In fact, when you brush me I go crazy and rub my face all over and roll around--it makes me so happy! I also will roll onto my back and like tummy rubs and will purr, purr, purr! However, I am shy at first, and wary of sudden movements or noises, so as long as you keep that in mind we should be able to be good friends. I have been at the House of Mews a very long time and I think people may overlook me just because I am shy? I like to eat canned cat food with my paw--it is so cute! On that note, once you adopt me, you are going to *have* to give me a canned food treat every once and a while...it is my favorite thing (well, maybe treats are my favorite thing too). The volunteer who is typing this for me (paws make that kind of difficult) says that I am one of her favorites...even though I don't think she is supposed to have favorites... Approx. DOB is 9/29/98.

I'm Toni, and in a word, can you resist that face? I came to the House of Mews with my four sisters and brothers (Trini, Trudy, Tansey and Adrian). I love to be brushed and petted, and always want to inspect what you are doing. I came to the House of Mews fearful, but I have progressed well and now I am just a little shy. But don't worry--I can even be picked up now and am a real lovebug! I am playful too. I am mostly white, with some black and white tabby spots on the top of head and my tail.  Approx. DOB is 2-28-06.

Hi! I'm Trudy. I am a pretty white kitty with large tabby patches on my back and head. I like to be petted and will flop on the floor for more lovin'. I like to talk (meow!) and I like to be brushed, well, most of the time. And I can go crazy batting around a toy, although it may not look like it from my photos. I came to the House of Mews with my 4 brothers and sisters (Trini, Toni, Adrian and Tansey), fearful, but I am sooooo much better now! Don't worry, I like people, I am still just shy in some ways. I like to play too. Canned food time is my favorite time of day! Approx. DOB is 2-28-06.

They call me Tansey and I am a white cat with tabby spots. I am a very handsome cat but "some people" think cats are supposed to sit in your lap, get petted, and brushed. Well, even though many of my House of Mews roommates go along with that theory, I am my own cat and will do what I please, thank you very much. I am curious and inquisitive (can't you tell from my expression?) but will keep my distance. However, in a quiet moment when I am in a basket, I will allow myself to be petted and I must admit it feels pretty good. I came to the House of Mews, fearful, with my 4 brothers and sisters (Adrian, Trini, Trudy and Toni) and just haven't figured out those silly humans yet. My brothers and sisters have decided they like humans for the most part, and they keep bugging me about it.....siblings! However, some people say that with a loving home, with a special loving and patient person, who is interested in working with fearful kitties, I might learn to open up some and become a bit more affectionate. Who knows? Approx. DOB is 3-24-06.

I'm Daisey, a Calico kitty but you can tell me apart from the other Calicos in this place because I have an all-black nose. You may see me around The House of Mews with my sister Poppy, or perhaps taking in the whole scene perched high on the cat walks or in a sunny window. I am a playful and curious kitty and I like toys on sticks. I like to be petted. Please come visit my sister and I today! We are soooo cute and soooo sweet. PS - Poppy and I would like to be adopted together. What is better than one cat? TWO! Approx. DOB is 10/7/06.

"Meow, meow, meow..." my name is Jacob and I am a BIG, handsome Siamese male. I am very sociable, affectionate and love attention. I have a great personality, I enjoy being petted and like to talk to you too! I am friendly with strangers and patient with children. I am playful and energetic, and my favorite toy is a wadded up piece of paper (see, I am economical too). When you sit on the couch I like to sit next to you and lay my paw on your lap. They say I am "quite a catch," and I have beautiful blue eyes that will melt your heart. I will flop down, roll over and show you my tummy. Everyone really seems to like me that meets me and say I am a real nice cat, so I bet you will think so too. Won't you come say hello... er.... "meow?" D.O.B. approx. 5-10-05.

Meow, I'm called Meggie and I am quite petite and have a sleek black coat and big green eyes. I was abandoned in a locked house for two weeks, then when I was freed I was forced to live on the streets! But that was a while ago and thankfully I currently reside safely at the House of Mews where I am in search of a patient and loving person who would like to be my new pet parent. You see, during my past life I didn't receive very much love and affection so I may not be quite as cuddly as some of my other roommates here. But I have warmed up a lot and now I am a sweet kitty and I enjoy being petted and brushed. I'll even ask you for your attention, so you better be ready to give it up when you come visit me at the House of Mews! Maybe with some extra TLC I know I will come out of my shell even more. Please don't overlook me because I am a little shy. I am a sweet (and did I mention pretty?) girl. Approx. DOB is 9/21/04.

My name is Apollo and I need a special home. Wait a minute, that sounded like a 12-step program meeting, letâs start over. I am a handsome, very large black male cat. I mean, I might be the biggest cat here at the House of Mews! I also have huge yellow eyes that can turn from almond-shape to huge round circles in seconds! I am very curious and inquisitive (why do you think I get those big eyes?). Anyway, I was abandoned (along with my siblings Bach and Aurora) and I guess I was never really socialized around people the way I should have been, and now I am somewhat fearful of people (and loud noises, like vacuums). If you want to pet me you just need to take it slow. Just choose a quiet moment, come on over, and slowly hold your hand out for me to sniff first. Depending on my mood, I sometimes like to be petted on my head and chin, and I even have been brushed a few times. Donât freak out if I hiss at you, itâs just my way of telling you I am a little scared at first. Would you want someone 10 times your size reaching out for you? Oh, and if you have TREATS, Iâll almost always let you pet me...well maybe just a little. However, maybe if a very special loving and patient person comes along, who is interested in working with fearful kitties, I might learn to open up some and become more affectionate. Who knows? Approx. DOB is 04/07/05.

Meow, my caregiver died so now I am in search of a new forever home all over again. I am a shy, sweet and affectionate lapcat. I like my head petted, and I really like it when you scratch me under my chin (and behind my ears too). I am OK with being brushed, and I need it too being that I am a long-haired cat. I am sure with a patient and loving new pet parent, I will come back out of my shell more and become a special companion for you. I have hopes that someone out there may have a special place in their heart for me and a little extra TLC, and give me a second chance. Everyone deserves one, you know... Approx DOB is 9-16-04.

I'm Mandy. If you are looking for an extremely loving and sweet cat, then I may be the right one for you! I love attention and being held. I will P-U-R-R and rub my head on your chin when you cuddle me. But I have a shy side and like to hide a lot to feel safe. As you can see from my picture I frequently will put my paws on your leg and meow to tell you I want to be held and loved. I will lay in your lap on my back and you can rub my tummy. The only other home I have known besides the House of Mews is a garage. Please come meet me soon! I know you're gonna love me!  I AM CURRENTLY BEING FOSTERED--CONTACT THE HOUSE OF MEWS IF INTERESTED IN ADOPTING ME.  Approx. DOB is 6-24-08.

Hi there, my name is Soho and I am a sleek black cat that also happens to be part Siamese. "Some people" think cats are supposed to sit in your lap, get petted, and brushed. Well, even though many of my other roommates go along with that theory, I am my own cat and will do what I please, thank you very much. I am curious and inquisitive and like to see what's going on, but I will keep my distance. I was abandoned early on in life and have just never figured out those humans yet. However, in a loving home, with a very special loving and patient person who is interested in working with fearful kitties, I might learn to open up some and become a bit more affectionate. Who knows? Approx. DOB is 9-2-03.

My name is Gwen, named after Gwen Stefani, but I am not all crazy and in your face like she is. I am a sweet and loving black cat, with just the smallest patch of white on my chest. I am gentle and quiet, yet curious, and enjoy affection. I LOVE to be brushed and I'll sit on your lap while you stroke me. I yearn for your love, but since I am a little quiet and shy, don't take it the wrong way if I hide for a little while when you take me home. Trust me, I will love you and want to be friends. I just need a little extra TLC to adjust to a big new place. Please give me a chance, 'cause I kinda get overlooked in here in favor of other cats who may be more forward and up in your business. But I promise I am just as nice a cat as any of them. One of the volunteers calls me one of her favorites, so it must be true? Approx. DOB is 9-15-08.

I'm Boots,and I am looking for a forever home. I am a sweet kitty, but am a little on the shy side. I think they call that reserved. I'll just need some extra TLC and patience, you know? I loved my best friend Mr. T who recently went over the rainbow bridge - we were together most of our lives. You could find us sometimes grooming each other and curled up together taking a nap. I  left a picture posted of us together in his honor. Oh yeah, if you think one of my eyes looks a little funny, I have a birth defect but it does not affect my vision depth or perception. Please come check me out, and don't overlook me just because I am shy. Approx. DOB is 6-16-03.

Susan is a cute petite Calico cat who was a stray and caught via trap in someone's yard. She gave birth to three kittens (Carl, Markie, and Billy) at The House of Mews. Look at what a good mommy she was (although her mommy days are over now). She is a sweet cat who loves her head scratched. She likes to sit in a basket and roll all around it and rub her head on every square inch. She is sure to make a loving companion for a lucky adopter. She is a little on the shy side sometimes, but probably nothing getting settled into a permanent loving home won't cure. Approx DOB is 9-9-07.

I'm Tizzie but I really don't get in a "tizzy" very often, in fact, I am a rather quiet cat. Well, I guess sometimes I do get a little crazy, if you walk up on me too fast, I may try to run away fast, and I look like those cartoons that run in place for a couple of seconds before I get myself moving. Although I can be a little timid, I am a sweet cat. You can put me on your lap and I will lay down and roll over while you pet me. I LOVE my tummy rubbed too. I like my head scratched and like to sleep in a basket. When you pet me in the basket I roll all around. Um, and I am a littlle, uh, fluffier now that in my picture. Yeah, fluffy, that's it. I do like my canned food. My kittens Torrence and Taylor are gone and it's just me now. Approx. DOB is 4-3-09.

Mew, I'm Two and my sister Indiana and I--both pastel calicos--are looking for a new home (please, please, please together). So you might think since we are adults that we are "old" cats. Well let me tell you we still act like kittens and are super playful--we like toys and playing with each other especially. We can leap to great heights. And might I add we look pretty darn cute while we're doing it. We have beautiful, long coats and big, fluffy tails. We still have our baby picture posted here because it just wouldn't be fair to deprave you of such a cute photo! Check out our video when we were kittens! I am a bit shyer than my sister Indiana but we balance each other out, right? Approx. DOB is 12-11-09.

Mew, I'm Indiana and my sister Two and I--both pastel calicos--are looking for a new home (please, please, please together).So you might think since we are adults that we are "old" cats. Well let me tell you we still act like kittens and are super playful--we like toys and playing with each other especially. We can leap to great heights. And might I add we look pretty darn cute while we're doing it. We have beautiful, long coats and big, fluffy tails. We still have our baby picture posted here because it just wouldn't be fair to deprave you of such a cute photo! Check out our video when we were kittens! My sister Two is a bit shyer than me, but we balance each other out, right? Approx. DOB is 12-11-09.

I am a beautiful little girl, and I have changed a lot since arriving at the House of Mews. When I was a baby I was scared of people... I would even forget my manners and hiss at you! I may still act shy or unsure, but it is totally obvious that I am seeking your affection. You can pet me and I may kind of run away, but then I come RIGHT BACK! I am kind of like a tease, I heard someone say. I will rub my face on stuff while you pet me, which means I like it. I like to be brushed too, and will lurk around hinting if you are brushing other cats instead of me. I will lay down and show you my pretty coat and I donât try and run away or anything while you are admiring me. If you put me on your lap, I may sit there for a little bit while you are petting me, but I think I just need some more warming up before I get too comfortable. I just need a new forever home where they will understand I just need a little extra TLC to make me feel comfortable and loved. Please come meet me and give me a chance. Approx DOB is 4-28-10.
One of eight kittens rescued from a crawlspace. He is playful and loveable, but also a bit on the shy side at first. Approx. DOB is 10/4/10.

One of eight kittens rescued from a crawlspace. When Lulu came to The House of Mews she was very shy, but she has come out of her shell and all she wants is to be petted and loved on. She will lay in your lap and will love every minute of it! Just keep petting her and you've found a friend for life. She will also talk to you (pretty loudly) to try and get you to pay her some attention. As you pick her up to put her on your lap don't mind her very loud meowing (almost screaming), she stops the SECOND she hits your lap. TRUST ME, she wants to be on your lap more than anything in the world!!! And look... she has a heart pattern in her coat! Approx. DOB is 10/4/10.

I was living outside cold and hungry, when I wandered upon a nice lady's porch. I meowed very loudly so she would hear me and come find me. I was fed and given a warm place to sleep for the night, but alas the lady already had too many cats so I couldn't stay. I am a small, black kitty, but have kind of a unique white/silver undercoat. I am loving and I love to cuddle, and crave your attention. I will sit on your lap, be held, and purr, purr, purr. I like toys on strings. I like to talk to you. I was named after blues singer Sippie Wallace--won't you come adopt me so I can stop singin' the blues?  Approx. DOB is 8/22/10.

I was rescued from a local kill shelter, where I would be put to sleep--whatever that means. I am a sweet, loving kitty. You may not notice me at first as I like to curl up for naps in a basket high above the floor. But once you come and acknowledge me, you will see I am yearning for your affection and love to be petted. I rub my head all over and roll around in the basket. You just gotta be sure and seek me out! And any cat that will wear a Santa hat sounds like a pretty good cat if I do say so myself. Approx. DOB is 4-1-10.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - orange and white

description.$t: I was found on the University of Memphis campus, under a large metal dumpster when I was a tiny kitten. A hawk was circling above - gulp! But I was rescued by a nice student. Whew! I am now all grown up and a BIG, handsome boy! I will greet you at the door and rub all over your legs and follow you around. I will lay in your lap and purr while you pet me. I also L-O-V-E plastic ball cat toys with a bell inside! I will chase it so fast, then hold it in my mouth and walk around claiming my victory. I will even bring the ball back to you! That's right, I FETCH--check out my video! Just try it while visiting The House of Mews, you'll see! Approx. DOB is 4/5/11.

All these boys! I'm the only female! I'm Rahab. I am the most mature of the group. I love to play but I am always high on my perch to watch the boys do their boy things. My brothers and I came to The House of Mews in June of 2011. We were fostered by a volunteer for over two months. We came in shy, covered in fleas and completely dirty. But we were cleaned up and brought to a nice comfy environment where we were socialized with a dog and two humans. Although I am still on the shy side, I am sweet and will usually be one of the first ones to greet you at the door at The House of Mews. Siblings are Abraham, Malachi, Potiphar, Ramesses, Titiana. Approx. DOB is 4/7/11.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - buff and white

description.$t: Hi, I'm Abraham. I am a sophisticated kitty. I have a shy, sweet demeanor, much like my siblings. Give me a pat on the head and a scratch behind my ears and you have my attention. I like to relax and receive love. I will sit next to you when you sit on the floor. I want to be adopted by someone that will love me and kiss my forehead every day. That's what my foster mommy did. I have been socialized with small dogs, but young children may not be suitable. Siblings are Rahab, Malachi, Potiphar, Ramesses, Titiana. Approx. DOB is 4/7/11.

breed.$t: Domestic Medium Hair - buff and white

description.$t: Malachi is my name. I love to play and I'm always in the mood for some canned treats. I will greet you at the door and rub all over your legs and follow you around. I will lay in your lap and purr while you pet me. I'm a big boy full of big love. Come meet me! Check out my big, fluffy tail! Siblings are Abraham, Rahab, Potiphar, Ramesses, Titiana. Approx. DOB is 4/7/11.

My name is Titiana (formerly Titus, oops, I am a girl not a boy) and I am a super lovebug in a tiny package! Seriously, just come visit me at The House of Mews and I will be all over you! Just sit down and I will start on your lap, then try to lay on your chest too since I want to be sooo close to you. I'll nuzzle your neck and chin, and of course purr the whole time I am doing it. Purrty please come meet me. Sometimes you may think I am a bit shy at first, but once I warm up I will love you! Siblings are Abraham, Malachi, Potiphar, Ramesses, Rahab. Approx. DOB is 4/7/11.

My siblings Nala, Carly and Tigger - and our mama Sparkle - were rescued from being put to sleep at the Memphis Animal Shelter. Actually, our mama was rescued before we were even born! Nala and TIgger and Mama were adopted but Carly and I are still here waiting for the right person to come to the door to take us home. I am sweet and laid back and can usually be found curled up catching a cat nap at the back of the store. But after napping I like to chase my friends around the catwalks. DOB is 4/28/11.

My siblings Nala, Ellie Mae and Tigger - and our mama Sparkle - were rescued from being put to sleep at the Memphis Animal Shelter. Nala and TIgger and Mama were adopted but Ellie Mae and I are still here waiting for the right person to come to the door to take us home. I have been told I have a charming and sweet personality and check out my striking markings! I also love to sit by the sink and watch the water run. DOB is 4/28/11.

I'm Katniss, named after the main character of "The Hunger Games" book (soon to be come a movie). I am a l-o-v-e-b-u-g! I crave your affection, love to be held, and really hope I get adopted soon! You've got to come meet me and see how sweet I am for yourself. I am high-energy with a little bit of sass too - that's called personality. Just like Katniss in The Hunger Games! Oh, and don't worry--that photo of me is a yawn, nothing more! I will lay on your lap and purr while you pet me too. I was rescued from being put to sleep at Memphis Animal Services. Siblings are Prim, Peeta and Juice; mother is Cherie. Approx. DOB is 3/16/11.

I was found at a movie theater in Bartlett when I was 2 months old. I was scared and hungry, and hiding in the bushes so those big cars wouldn't run over me. I am a laid-back kitty who is sweet and affectionate. I love to be petted, especially on my chin, and I like tummy rubs too. Some people think I am a bit shy, and it's true I may take a bit longer to get adjusted in a new home, but I know we will become the best of friends if you just give me a chance and a little bit of patience. Approx. DOB is 10/13/08.

I love to run and play and chase all my friends at The House of Mews. I'm very friendly and am always one of the first ones to the door when you enter The House of Mews. I will follow you around and I love to be petted! Mother is Ella and sister is Holly III. Approx. DOB is 7/1/11.

Mother is Ella and brother is Buddy. Holly III is full of life and has lots of personality, as most Torties do! She loves to play and chase cat toys all over the place. She would LOVE to find her fur-ever person to LOVE always. Approx. DOB is 7/1/11.

breed.$t: Domestic Long Hair - gray and white

description.$t: My previous caregiver moved to the west coast and I was left with her father. Now he has to move to a new place that doesn't allow pets. So my partner, Cally Cat, and I now reside at The House of Mews. I am an affectionate cat, but am a little shy and still getting used to this new place... Yeah, I guess I am classified as a senior cat, but hey, there are benfits to adopting a senior cat - since you are already online just Google it why don't you? Approx. DOB is 1/7/02.

This cat family was rescued from being put to sleep at a local kill shelter. This is a whole family of sweethearts! Violet was tiny and was the smallest in the litter, but she seems to be all caught up now! She is playful and energetic and loves to have her head rubbed. She loves attention! (Mother is Petunia and siblings are Pansey, Sweet William, Jonquil, Cosmo, Aster.) Approx. DOB is 2/17/12.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - gray and white

description.$t: I'm Chip and I am affectionate, friendly and playful. My favorite place to chill out is in the wringer part of the mop bucket. I fit in just right. My brother Spiffy and sister Cookie and I were abandoned. Approx. DOB is 3/22/12.
Frankie along with siblings Bonnie, April and Claudia were rescued from a local kill shelter. He is a loving and animated sweetheart. Approx. DOB is 6/15/09.
Bonnie was rescued from a local kill shelter along with siblings April, Frankie and Claudia. She is very sweet and loves to have her head rubbed. Approx. DOB is 6/15/09.

Claudia along with her siblings April, Frankie and Bonnie were rescued from a local kill shelter. She loves to hang out where all the action is during adoption hours to make sure she gets lots of head rubs and ear scratches. Approx. DOB is 6/15/09.

I'm Tablet, and me and my mama Tabs used to live outside as strays. I'll admit I am on the shy side, but I am a sweet cat and and crave your affection. I have come SO FAR out of my shell. I like to be petted and if you keep at it for a while I will start purring. I even try and grab your hand after you stop petting me! I may even flop over on my side and bat your fingers around. When a House of Mews volunteer calls my name and squats down, I come running to her! I like playing with a ribbon. I will also lick and nuzzle your toes! I just know if someone could spend even more one-on-one time with me I would come out of my shell even more. I bet I would be a good reward for some extra love and patience? And hey, don't you really want a more chill cat vs. one of those that is always causing some kind of trouble? Approx. DOB is 3/18/12.

We all live here at The House of Mews now, whew! I am a very sweet, yet a little shy, pretty girl. I will roll around and bat my pretty green eyes at you, and I like playing with a ribbon. I have beautiful tabby markings and a spotted tummy. Super cute if I do say so myself. Oh, and check out my video that my rescuer took. She and her husband loved me a lot and were quite attached to me and Tablet while we lived in their yard. They moved away but they email to check up on how me and Tablet are doing. It would make her day if we got adopted... hint hint. Approx. DOB is 2/18/11.

Franz has some special health needs and so needs an owner who is willing to deal with that. He is also declawed. Both boys are neutered and current on their shots and are indoor only cats. So she gave me and my sister Callie up--we try to understand but it is hard. I am a bit shy and I may hide under the bed or couch until I become comfortable in my situation. Just don't force attention on me and allow me to make friends with you on my own terms. I just have to make sure that I feel safe. When I came to The House of Mews I was quite scared and shy, but now I enjoy affection of my visitors and have warmed up a lot and like to be petted by everyone. However she has not been eating since arriving at The House of Mews and after medication and force feeding she eventually had to have stomach surgery on 8/18/15 to remove what the vet thought was a mixture of packing tape and easter grass.
